    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small pieces of storage furniture built into or hung on a wall near the main altar, in the baptistery, or in the sacristy to contain the holy oils. The door, which must be kept locked, sometimes bears the words "Olea Sancta."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049837/Thesaurus des Objets Religieux (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleine meubels waarin men de heilige oliën bewaart en die in een muur zijn ingebouwd of daaraan zijn bevestigd, dicht bij het altaar, in de doopkapel of in de sacristie. Op de deur, die men op slot moet houden, staan soms de woorden ���Olea Sancta'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text> 教堂的洗禮堂或聖器室內，可嵌於或掛在牆上的小件儲藏家具，靠近主祭壇，用以盛裝聖油。櫃門必須上鎖，上面有時會標示拉丁文「聖油（Olea Sancta）」兩字。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
